# Astro Blog Developer Skill

Use this rule when working on this Astro blog, especially for content writing, post editing, content collections, Markdown/MDX pipelines, routing, layouts, RSS, sitemap, SEO metadata, image optimization, deployment configuration, and performance tuning.

## Baseline Checks

- Identify the Astro version, adapter, package manager, and deployment target before making structural changes.
- Map the content source: local Markdown, MDX, CMS, or hybrid.
- Check TypeScript strictness, lint scripts, build scripts, and available tests.

## Content Writing And Modeling

- Prefer Astro content collections with explicit schemas.
- Keep frontmatter strict and predictable.
- Require core fields for posts: `title`, `description`, `pubDate`, `slug`, `tags`, and `draft`.
- Treat `description` as a real search/social summary, not filler.
- Keep slugs stable and avoid breaking existing URLs.
- Handle `draft` posts and future dates explicitly.
- Sort published lists deterministically by publish date.

## Routes And Rendering

- Prefer static-first rendering.
- Add SSR only when there is a clear product requirement.
- Use file-based routes and `getStaticPaths` for post pages.
- Keep tag archives, pagination, and post lists stable and predictable.
- Centralize slug and URL logic in reusable utilities.

## Layout, SEO, And Sharing

- Centralize metadata in a shared layout or metadata utility.
- Include canonical URLs, Open Graph tags, Twitter Card tags, and structured data where appropriate.
- Provide clear fallback behavior when optional image metadata is missing.
- Generate and validate `sitemap.xml` and RSS/Atom feeds.
- Ensure robots directives match the deployment environment.

## Performance And UX

- Minimize client hydration; use islands only where interaction adds real value.
- Use Astro image tooling with an intentional width and format strategy.
- Check home, post list, tag archive, and post detail pages for Core Web Vitals-sensitive regressions.
- Keep writing pages readable, fast, and accessible on mobile and desktop.

## Validation

- Run build, type checks, linting, or targeted tests when relevant.
- Smoke-test paginated lists, tag pages, drafts, future-dated posts, and missing-content paths after route changes.
- Update or add tests when changing routing, sorting, metadata generation, RSS, sitemap, or content schema behavior.

## Implementation Rules

- Match existing project patterns before introducing new abstractions.
- Keep edits scoped to the blog feature or content being changed.
- Preserve backward-compatible URLs during migrations.
- Do not loosen content schemas to make invalid content pass.
- Prefer durable Astro APIs over ad hoc string manipulation.
